2. Polyostotic fibrous dysplasia with endocrine dysfunction
3. Congenital adrenal hyperplasia (CAH) due to 21-hydroxylase deficiency
4. Marfan syndrome with endocrine manifestations
5. Neurofibromatosis type 1 (NF1) with early puberty and endocrine abnormalities
6. Tuberous sclerosis complex (TSC) with hormonal and developmental issues
7. Beckwith-Wiedemann syndrome (BWS) with endocrine and genital anomalies
8. Russell-Silver syndrome (RSS) with early puberty and cafe-au-lait spots
9. Carney complex with endocrine overactivity and skin pigmentation
10. Ataxia telangiectasia with endocrine and developmental abnormalities. 

Please note that these are potential diagnoses based on the clinical presentation provided, and further diagnostic testing would be required to confirm any of these conditions.
